					<description><![CDATA[I decided to start on an English paper piecing project to have some hand sewing to do whilst travelling or watching the television. I wanted]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>I decided to start on an English paper piecing project to have some hand sewing to do whilst travelling or watching the television. I wanted to do large hexagons which would all fit together nicely, but not all be the same design. Different designs would be more interesting for me to sew, and I could learn more by doing different designs. After ordering some triangular graph paper, I set to work on some designs.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-7 is-layout-flex">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="1024" data-id="212"  src="/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005-1024x1024.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-212" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005-1024x1024.jpeg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005-300x300.jpeg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005-150x150.jpeg 150w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005-768x768.jpeg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005-800x800.jpeg 800w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_005.jpeg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



