<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1024" height="1024" data-id="209"  src="/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004-1024x1024.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-209" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004-1024x1024.jpeg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004-300x300.jpeg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004-150x150.jpeg 150w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004-768x768.jpeg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004-800x800.jpeg 800w, /wp-content/uploads/2023/06/signal-2023-06-22-121220_004.jpeg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</figure>



<p>This quilt will be made solely out of scraps as the pieces are small, it is the perfect project for scraps. My idea for the final quilt is that it will be quite a hodgepodge of different fabrics as I am not going to abide by any colour scheme, anything goes! This quilt will probably take a lifetime, but I don&#8217;t mind too much about that.</p>



